## Sermon

Beloved in the Lord, grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and from Christ Jesus our Lord.
As we consider this season of Epiphany, we ask, "Where does Christ shine in our own lives?"
Our Old Testament reading in Isaiah reminds us, "What kind of trouble are we in if we are in the presence of God`'_RQ()s glory?"
Christ is shining and we are sinners---how do we take this?



**"And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus"** [(Php 4:7 ESV)](https://www.esv.org/Philippians+4:7/).
AMEN.

