## Notes

This is a Communion Sunday. What the angel took from the altar with tongs achieves the same thing as Holy Communion: "_TOUCHED_YOUR_LIPS"

Joash renovated the temple with the help of Jehoiada the priest c. 812 B.C. (2Ch 24:4‑14).
After Jehoiada's death, the king began to listen to the princes of Judah and led Judah back into idolatry (2Ch 24:17‑19).
Zechariah, Jehoiada's son, spoke out and was stoned; Joash allowed it to happen (2Ch 24:20‑22).
After Joash, was assassinated, Amaziah reigned in his place.
Amaziah slaughtered Edomites, but then turned and worshiped their gods (2Ch 25:11‑16).[^1]
Amaziah's son Azariah (Uzziah) became king in his place (2Ch 26).
But when he grew strong, Azariah became proud and entered the temple to burn incense himself, as the priests were called to do.
For this, leprosy broke out on Azariah's forehead while he was in the temple being confronted by the priests. Azariah was a leper to the day of his death (2Ch 26:16ff).

[^1]: I couldn't find out much about Edomite gods without subscribing to *Biblical Archaeology Review*.